## 2026-03-27 - updateAliasRefs only handles simple string $value
- Both `updateAliasRefs` and `updateBulkAliasRefs` now handle composite/object `$value` fields (e.g. shadow `{ color: "{color.primary}" }`). When `$value` is an object, a dedicated `updateCompositeValue` walker updates alias strings in all nested properties.
- Previously, the walk function recursed into objects but only checked `key === '$value'` for string replacement, so sub-properties like `color`, `offsetX` inside composite values were never updated during renames.
- Files changed: `packages/server/src/services/token-store.ts` ~L625 (updateAliasRefs), ~L665 (updateBulkAliasRefs)

